From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Amaan Qureshi <git@amaanq.com>
Date: Sat, 14 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 12/14] octeon: load modules into the sign-extended CKSSEG segment

Clang has no -msym32 so modules load into XKSEG, where the module loader's
HIGHER/HIGHEST relocs mangle their addresses and crash .ko loads. Drop the
sym32 gate so modules load at CKSSEG instead.

Signed-off-by: Amaan Qureshi <git@amaanq.com>
---
diff --git a/arch/mips/include/asm/pgtable-64.h b/arch/mips/include/asm/pgtable-64.h
--- a/arch/mips/include/asm/pgtable-64.h
+++ b/arch/mips/include/asm/pgtable-64.h
@@ -144,8 +144,7 @@
 	 min(PTRS_PER_PGD * PTRS_PER_PUD * PTRS_PER_PMD * PTRS_PER_PTE * PAGE_SIZE, \
 	     (1UL << cpu_vmbits)) - (1UL << 32))
 
-#if defined(CONFIG_MODULES) && defined(KBUILD_64BIT_SYM32) && \
-	VMALLOC_START != CKSSEG
+#if defined(CONFIG_MODULES) && VMALLOC_START != CKSSEG
 /* Load modules into 32bit-compatible segment. */
 #define MODULES_VADDR	CKSSEG
 #define MODULES_END	(FIXADDR_START-2*PAGE_SIZE)
